          <Comment>This sequence change creates a premature translational stop signal (p.Trp499Cysfs*7) in the CHD2 gene. It is expected to result in an absent or disrupted protein product. Loss-of-function variants in CHD2 are known to be pathogenic (PMID: 23708187, 24207121). This variant is not present in population databases (ExAC no frequency). This variant has not been reported in the literature in individuals affected with CHD2-related conditions. For these reasons, this variant has been classified as Pathogenic.</Comment>
